docs.abstract: Gas was seen as a bridge from coal to an alternative-energy future. Regulatory moves to speed that transition have unsettled the utility industry.

docs.lead_paragraph: As environmental concerns drive power companies away from using coal, natural gas has emerged as the nation’s No. 1 power source. headline.main: It’s the No. 1 Power Source, but Natural Gas Faces Headwinds
